Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A pill-shaped floating action button, bottom-right of every page:
- Open chat (side panel via user-gesture relay), Add this page to
  board, Pin a spot, Highlight text — community selector when in
  more than one community
- Honest empty state when in no community; hidden when not onboarded
- Toggleable from BOTH sides: 'Hide pill' in the pill's own menu, and
  a 'Tabcom pill on pages' switch in Settings (with a visible Build
  M14 marker). Reacts live via storage.onChanged — no reload needed.

Clean-file architecture:
- src/content/page-pill.ts: fully self-contained — own shadow root,
  own styles, storage-driven, zero coupling to the annotation overlay;
  host actions injected via a 4-function interface
- src/lib/pill-settings.ts: one storage flag (get/set/subscribe),
  deliberately outside zustand

Also the three wiring fixes the pill's actions require:
- transports:['websocket'] (polling needs XHR — absent in MV3 service
  workers; every background write silently failed without this)
- 'item_add' relay action in the background
- 'tabcom:open-panel' handler (sidePanel.open for the sender tab)

Verified by executing the built content.js in a simulated DOM: FAB
renders, menu opens with 5 actions, pin rendering and pin-mode
composer flows still pass. 27/27 server tests at this HEAD.
